On large JIRA deployments with many projects, there will be some permission schemes which do not use all of the roles that are defined in the system. For example, we have some permission schemes which use a "Testers" role, and others which do not. When a project administrator edits roles for a project where the permission scheme does not use the "Testers" role, that role still appears in the list. For many of our users, this leads to confusion.

